message.content:
I need to identify the total amount of liabilities and equity in the balance sheet, along with its component sub-items.

Looking at the balance sheet, I can see the line item "Total Liabilities and Owner's Equity" which has:
- Initial value: 13000000.00 (as of 2023-12-31)
- End value: 14214117.02 (as of 2024-02-05)

This item is composed of two main sub-items:
1. "Total Current Liabilities"
   - Initial value: 0.00 (2023-12-31)
   - End value: 378850.51 (2024-02-05)

2. "Total Owner's Equity"
   - Initial value: 13000000.00 (2023-12-31)
   - End value: 13835266.51 (2024-02-05)

When you add these two sub-items:
0.00 + 13000000.00 = 13000000.00 (initial)
378850.51 + 13835266.51 = 14214117.02 (end)

This confirms these are the correct components that make up the total liabilities and equity.

```json
{"solution": {'initial value': '13000000.00', 'end value': '14214117.02', 'sub_items': {'initial sub_item value1': '0.00', 'end sub_item value1': '378850.51', 'initial sub_item value2': '13000000.00', 'end sub_item value2': '13835266.51'}}}
```
